{"flatpakAppId":"com.valvesoftware.Steam.desktop","name":"Steam (installer)","summary":"Launcher for the Steam software distribution service","description":"\n    <p>Steam is a software distribution service with an online store, automated\n      installation, automatic updates, achievements, SteamCloud synchronized\n      savegame and screenshot functionality, and many social features.</p>\n    <p>This unofficial package provides a script that downloads and installs\n      the Steam client, and depends on 32-bit and 64-bit libraries and\n      other components that are required by the Steam client. The actual\n      Steam installation and all Steam games will be installed into the\n      home directory of each user who runs the installer script.</p>\n    <p>Because Steam requires 32-bit libraries, before installing this package\n      it will be necessary to run, as root:\n      <code>dpkg --add-architecture i386; apt update</code></p>\n  ","developerName":null,"projectLicense":"LicenseRef-proprietary","homepageUrl":"https://store.steampowered.com","donationUrl":null,"translateUrl":null,"bugtrackerUrl":"https://github.com/ValveSoftware/steam-for-linux/issues","helpUrl":null,"categories":[{"name":"Game"},{"name":"PackageManager"}],"downloadFlatpakRefUrl":"steam-installer","currentReleaseVersion":"1.0.0.78","currentReleaseDescription":null,"iconDesktopUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble/com/valvesoftware/Steam.desktop/ce08244456022febc908c68d964868a5/icons/128x128/steam-installer_steam.png","iconMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble/com/valvesoftware/Steam.desktop/ce08244456022febc908c68d964868a5/icons/128x128/steam-installer_steam.png","screenshots":[{"thumbUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble/com/valvesoftware/Steam.desktop/ce08244456022febc908c68d964868a5/screenshots/image-1_224x191.png","imgMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/noble/com/valvesoftware/Steam.desktop/ce08244456022febc908c68d964868a5/screenshots/image-1_75